commitResults.messageTitle: Add Student, NusNetId, UniqueSudentInTutorialList classes to seedu.address.person package
commitResults.messageBody: The Student class represents a Person with an NusNetId and a TutorialName. All fields are present and not null in a Student object, i.e. every Student must be within a Tutorial and a non-Student Person should not be within a Tutorial.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Assessment and relevant data field classes to seedu.address.model.assessment package
commitResults.messageBody:
An Assessment contains AssessmentName, Weightage and FullMark fields. It does not contain the student's results. The reason for this is because a non-Tutorial-specific Assessment class is helpful if the team chooses to implement commands like `list assessments` or `edit assessment`.

Each Assessment is associated with an AssessmentResults (present in a later commit).

commitResults.messageTitle: Add UniqueAssessmentList and related exceptions to seedu.address.model.assessment package
commitResults.messageBody:
UniqueAssessmentList is a list containing all the Assessment objects in the address book. It enforces uniqueness among the elements using the AssessmentName as the identifier.

This class is useful for listing assessments or editing an assessment.

Its backing list is an ObservableList which has the benefit of allowing listeners to track changes to the list (so that the UI can update the list of assessments automatically when there is a change in the UniqueAssessmentList).

See UniquePersonList in the model.person package and PersonListPanel in the ui package for reference.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add AssessmentResultsList, AssessmentResults and StudentResult classes to seedu.address.model.assessment package
commitResults.messageBody:
StudenResult represents the result of a single student for an assessment and contains an NusNetId and Score.
AssessmentResults contains a list of StudentResults and has an AssessmentName (is associated with an Assessment).
AssessmentResultsList contains a list of AssessmentResults and has a TutorialName (inside a Tutorial).

An AssessmentResultsList is associated with a Tutorial while the UniqueAssessmentList is associated with the ModelManager or AddresBook.

AssessmentResults and AssessmentResultsList both contain ObservableLists for the same reason as in the previous commit.

Note: the AssessmentNotFoundException is meant for the previous commit but DuplicateStudentResultException is added in the previous commit by accident.

Add a Tutorial and related data field classes to seedu.address.model.tutorial
commitResults.messageBody:
A Tutorial represents a class managed by the TA (it is named Tutorial to avoid confusion and errors with Java Class).
A Tutorial contains a TutorialName, Day, Time, UniqueStudentsInTutorialList and AssessmentResultsList.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add a field called allStudents, which contains all students in the address book to ModelManager class
commitResults.messageBody:
allStudents is declared as a FilteredList<Person>, which takes in the address book's persons list and a predicate to filter the students.

allStudents is automatically updated when the address book's person list is updated (this has been manually tested on a smaller scale) so there is no need to manually update allStudents.

More changes need to be done to ModelManager and/or AddressBook to include new data classes.

Add a UniqueTutorialList class and related exception class to tutorial package
commitResults.messageBody: The UniqueTutorialList class represents a list of Tutorials in the address book that enforces uniqueness between its elements. It is useful for operations such as adding or removing tutorials from the model.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add a tutorial list and assessment list to AddressBook class to integrate new data classes into model
commitResults.messageBody:
AddressBook wraps all the data at the address-book level, including the persons, tutorials and assessments. It provides methods for updating the lists of persons, tutorials and assessments which are used by the ModelManager to update the model components after a command is executed.

Todo: add methods for updating the tutorial list and assessment list in the AddressBook and ModelManager classes (update the Model interface as well).
